ExecDesc.value: RealNetworks RealPlayer QCP Parsing Buffer Overflow(IPv6 Version)

EngDesc.value: A heap buffer overflow exists in RealNetworks RealPlayer. The vulnerability is due to insufficient bounds checking while copying user-supplied data into a fixed-length buffer. This can lead to a buffer overflow and subsequent memory corruption. A remote attacker can exploit this vulnerability by enticing a user to download and process a malicious QCP file with a vulnerable version of the application. A successful attack would result in the execution of attacker-controlled code in the security context of the current user.
